The Bytes value type, BytesReader, and BytesWriter are an original Swift
design specified by bare-swift RFC-0006:

  https://github.com/bare-swift/bare-swift/blob/main/rfcs/0006-bytes-buffer-type.md

Design influences include the Rust `bytes` crate
(https://crates.io/crates/bytes, MIT) and the Swift evolution proposals
for `Span<T>` and `RawSpan`. No third-party source is included.
